==English==

===Etymology===
An Irish word that appears in English literature and political speech.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a fool, someone who is out of their senses, simpleton.

===Examples===
"No, you omadhaun.  It bites your shoulder, rips it right off."
--Frank McCourt, Angela's Ashes, 1996.

"...an Omadhaun is a man who began life with some sense, but lost most of it on his journey."
--Andrew Barton ‘Banjo’ Paterson, A Story of Outback Life, 1906.